11 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
12 An Act relating to the Oklahoma Turnpike Authority;
amending 69 O.S. 2021, Section 1705, as amended by
13 Section 572, Chapter 486, O.S.L. 2025 (69 O.S. Supp.
2025, Section 1705), which relates to the powers and
14 duties of the Oklahoma Turnpike Authority; removing
authorization for Authority for construction at
15 certain locations; altering location of certain
authorized construction; removing certain bond
16 issuance requirement; updating statutory language;
amending 69 O.S. 2021, Section 1717, which relates to
17 project to become part of state highway system;
modifying conditions for a turnpike to become part of
18 the state highway system; and providing an effective
date.
19
20
21 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
22 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 69 O.S. 2021, Section 1705, as
23 amended by Section 572, Chapter 486, O.S.L. 2025 (69 O.S. Supp.
24 2025, Section 1705), is amended to read as follows:
Req. No. 17494 Page 1

1 Section 1705. The Oklahoma Turnpike Authority is hereby
2 authorized and empowered:
3 (a) To adopt bylaws for the regulation of its affairs and
4 conduct of its business.
5 (b) To adopt an official seal and alter the same at pleasure.
6 (c) To maintain an office at such place or places within the
7 state as it may designate.
8 (d) To sue and be sued in contract, reverse condemnation,
9 equity, mandamus, and similar actions in its own name, plead and be
10 impleaded; provided, that any and all actions at law or in equity
11 against the Authority shall be brought in the county in which the
12 principal office of the Authority shall be located, or in the county
13 of the residence of the plaintiff, or the county where the cause of
14 action arose. All privileges granted to the Authority and duties
15 enjoined upon the Authority by the provisions of Sections 1701
16 through 1734 1736 of this title may be enforced in a court of
17 competent jurisdiction in an action in mandamus.
18 (e) To construct, maintain, repair, and operate turnpike
19 projects and highways, with their access and connecting roads, at
20 such locations and on such routes as it shall determine to be
21 feasible and economically sound; provided, that until specifically
22 authorized by the Legislature, the Authority shall be authorized to
23 construct and operate toll turnpikes only at the following
24 locations:
