Req. No. 17494 Page 12

1 (n) To do all things necessary or convenient to carry out the
2 powers expressly granted in Sections 1701 through 1734 1736 of this
3 title. The design standards for all paving shall comply with the
4 design standards of the American Association of State Highway and
5 Transportation Officials as modified by the Oklahoma Department of
6 Transportation. All contracts for construction work on turnpike
7 projects shall be let to the lowest responsible bidder, or bidders,
8 after notice by publication in a newspaper published in the county
9 where the work is to be done in two consecutive weekly issues of the
10 newspaper. In all cases where more than eight (8) miles of
11 construction is let at the same time and is not an advertisement for
12 a surface-treatment-only project, such advertisement shall provide
13 for bids on sections of the turnpike not to exceed eight (8) miles.
14 If the project advertised is a surface-treatment-only project of
15 more than twenty (20) miles of road, the advertisement shall provide
16 for bids on sections of the road no longer than twenty (20) miles,
17 as well as bids on the project as a whole. Subject to the following
18 restrictions and limitations, the Authority shall, when contracting
19 for construction work, divide such work into paving projects, bridge
20 projects, including underpasses and overpasses, and earthmoving or
21 miscellaneous projects, according to the type of work to be done.
22 Each project shall be let under a separate contract or contracts and
23 no contract or project shall include more than one of such types of
24 construction work. Each contract for construction work shall
Req. No. 17494 Page 13

1 cont ain a provision that ninety percent (90%) of all labor employed
2 on the project shall be residents of Oklahoma. However, contracts
3 for bridges may include earthwork and structures for the approaches
4 thereto.
5 (o) It shall be unlawful for any member, officer or employee of
6 the Authority to transact with the Authority, either directly or
7 indirectly, any business for profit of such member, officer, or
8 employee; and any person, firm, or corporation knowingly
9 participating therein shall be equally liable for violation of this
10 provision.
11 The term “business for profit” shall include, but not be limited
12 to, the acceptance or payment of any fee, commission, gift, or
13 consideration to such member, officer, or employee.
14 Violation of this provision shall constitute a Class D1 felony
15 offense punishable by incarceration as provided for in subsections B
16 through F of Section 20N of Title 21 of the Oklahoma Statutes, or a
17 fine of not less than Five Hundred Dollars ($500.00) and not more
18 than Five Thousand Dollars ($5,000.00), or both such imprisonment
19 and fine.
20 (p) In the event of a national emergency, the Authority,
21 subject to any vested rights or claims, may enter into contracts
22 with the federal government or any authorized agency thereof to
23 allow the federal government or agency thereof to use such turnpikes
24 partly or exclusively during the existence of such emergency,
Req. No. 17494 Page 14

1 prov ided, that the federal government agrees in such contract to
2 pay, during the term of such contract, an amount sufficient, when
3 added to any tolls collected, to meet all operating and maintenance
4 expenses, interest payments, and the minimum sinking fund and
5 reserve requirements of the trust agreement for the turnpike covered
6 by the contract.
7 (q) All meetings of the Authority shall be open public
8 meetings, and all records shall be public records, except when
9 considering personnel or litigation.
10 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 69 O.S. 2021, Section 1717, is
11 amended to read as follows:
12 Section 1717. When all bonds issued under the provisions of
13 this article and the interest thereon shall have been paid for a
14 period of ten (10) years or a sufficient amount for the payment of
15 all such bonds and the interest thereon to the maturity thereof
16 shall have been set aside in trust for the benefit of the
17 bondholders, such projects, if then in good condition and repair to
18 the satisfaction of the Commission having required no maintenance
19 expense for a period of ten (10) years and no known maintenance
20 needs forthcoming, shall become part of the state highway system and
21 shall thereafter be maintained by the Commission free of tolls.
22 Provided, that when all bonds for any turnpike project and the
23 interest thereon shall have been paid or such provision for payment
24 made, prior to payment of the bonds and interest on any other
Req. No. 17494 Page 15

1 proj ect or projects, such project shall continue to be operated as a
2 toll facility at toll rates not less than the lowest rate being
3 charged on any project, until all bonds issued by the Authority and
4 the interest thereon shall have been paid or such provisions for
5 payment made. The revenues of such paid-out projects shall be used
6 and applied by the Authority in paying the obligations or depositing
7 in the sinking fund of such other turnpike projects in the following
8 order: (a) To any project or projects in default on interest: (b)
9 to any project or projects in default on principal; (c) to any
10 project or projects having insufficient reserves or sinking fund
11 under its trust agreement. If all such other projects have
12 sufficient reserves then the revenues from such paid-out project
13 shall be prorated between such other projects on the basis of the
14 outstanding bonds of each project. If two or more projects fall
15 within any of the above categories, then the revenues shall be
16 prorated between them on the basis of the outstanding bonds of each
17 project.
18 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
